In the philosophy of science we sometimes find the opinion that modern
theories cannot be formulated without theoretic auxiliary concepts. On
the contrary I have formulated the task of obtaining every physical
theory in a form free of theoretic auxiliary concepts. I have shown that
this is possible for quantum mechanics \[178\]. Such a form of theory is
best suited to investigate all possible new theoretic concepts.
